mmoned you to put a curse on my enemies, but instead, you have blessed them these three times. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now go to your home! I said I would reward you richly, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 22:17","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" but look, the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" has denied you a reward.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 22:17","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Balaam answered Balak, “Didn’t I previously tell the messengers you sent me: "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go against the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s command, to do anything good or bad of my own will? I will say whatever the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 22:18","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 22:38","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":38,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 22:18","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":18},{"label":"Nm 22:38","book":"Num","chapter":22,"verse":38}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now I am going back to my people, but first, let me warn you what these people will do to your people in the future.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:24:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he proclaimed his poem:"},{"kind":"text","text":" The oracle of Balaam son of Beor,"},{"kind":"text","text":" the oracle of the man whose eyes are opened;"}],"crossRefs":[],"fo